  "title": "Sales Executive Alcohol Industry",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Highlights:</strong></p><p>• Organisation With Clear Direction, Mission, Vision and Core Values</p><p>• Dynamic Working Environment</p><p>• Stable Career Growth</p><p>• Basic ($2800 - $3500) + Allowance + Uncapped Commission</p><p>• Staff Benefits</p><p>• Performance Incentive</p><p>• On Job Training Provided<br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>• Generating leads</p><p>• Preparing weekly and monthly reports</p><p>• Preparing and submitting sales orders</p><p>• Visiting and negotiating with clients to evaluate needs or promote alcoholic beverage and services.</p><p>• Provide trustworthy feedback and after-sales support, continuously improve through feedback</p><p>• Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>• Working experience in FMCG sales or marketing preferred</p><p>• Knowledge of alcoholic beverage will be an advantage</p><p>• Diploma or Degree in business, marketing, economics, or related field</p><p>• Understanding of the sales process and dynamics</p><p>• Excellent written, communication, negotiation and presentation skills</p><p>• Territory management</p><p>• Able to work comfortably in a fast paced environment</p><p>• Competency in computers, microsoft office, BRM and CRM systems</p><p>• Possess class 3 driving licence</p><p>• Possess own vehicle will be an advantage</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Interested candidates are invited to submit your resume.</p>",
